\title{fiber categories and vertical maps}

\import{frct-0000}


\p{Let #{E} be a category displayed over #{B}. A \em{vertical map} in #{E} is defined to be one that lies over the identity map in #{B}. For every #{b\in B}, there the collection #{E\Sub{b}} of displayed objects has the structure of a category; in particular, we set #{\Hom{E\Sub{b}}{u}{v}} to be the collection of vertical maps #{u\DispTo{\Idn{b}}v}.}